HEADWORD: Lipans
<hw>Li*pans"</hw> <pr>(l⟦esl⟧*p⟦aum⟧nz")</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>;
<sing>sing. <singw>Lipan</singw> <pr>(l⟦esl⟧*p⟦aum⟧n")</pr>.</sing>
<fld>(Ethnol.)</fld> <def>A tribe of North American Indians, inhabiting
the northern part of Mexico. They belong to the Tinneh stock, and are
closely related to the Apaches.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

